<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="724" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="16.[1472,2676,291,560]" pageId="16" pageNumber="724">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1474,1843,291,324]" pageId="16" pageNumber="724">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. The Philippine Tree Squirrel is widespread, locally abundant, and considered a crop pest in certain areas. It is common in the local pet trade and could also be hunted locally for food. The effect of both of these potential threats is not well known, but may not be great.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
